# Generation 290: deductive syllogism from NATURAL surface forms (basic-chat
# cat.7 "Logica deduttiva", prompts 122 & 125). The reasoning core — apply the
# premises to a scratch KB and resolve the closing yes/no question — already
# existed (gen231) for the packed "if <p1> and <p2>, <q>?" shape. gen290 routes
# two more surface forms to that SAME core: the multi-sentence "P1. P2. Q?" form
# and the conjunction form WITHOUT a trailing '?'. Base is hermetic here (no world
# facts), so every Yes below is genuine inference on parrot0's own engine, not a
# recalled answer.

# Multi-sentence, period-separated (basic-chat prompt 122).
> Socrates is a man. All men are mortal. Is Socrates mortal?
< Yes.
# Novel symbols: proves the deduction is real, not a memorized fact.
> zorb is a blit. all blits are fumps. is zorb a fump?
< Yes.
# The "if <premises>, is <q>" conjunction WITHOUT a trailing '?' (prompt 125).
> if all cats are mammals and Tom is a cat, is Tom a mammal
< Yes.
# A three-step rule chain (man -> human -> mortal) still resolves.
> plato is a man. all men are humans. all humans are mortal. is plato mortal?
< Yes.
# A distractor premise about another class is simply ignored (it asserts fine but
# does not bear on the query). Every premise must parse as knowledge, though: an
# unparseable one makes the whole deduction decline rather than guess.
> aristotle is a man. all dogs are loyal. all men are mortal. is aristotle mortal?
< Yes.
# Honesty: an invalid inference is refused, not rubber-stamped. "animal" is a
# known predicate (from the cats rule) but rex is a dog, so the answer is No.
> rex is a dog. all cats are animals. is rex an animal?
< No.
# Ordinary multi-sentence prose is NOT hijacked into a false deduction: the
# premises do not assert as knowledge, so the router declines honestly.
> the sky is blue. grass is green. is water wet?
< I don't understand that yet.

# --- gen326 (TODO.md P5): the UNIVERSAL conclusion ---------------------------
# gen231 could only resolve a GROUND question ("is socrates a mortal?"). Asked the
# universal form the SAME premises entail, it walled — there is no individual to
# look up. A universal is now proved the way a universal is actually proved: an
# ARBITRARY WITNESS of the subject class is asserted into the scratch KB the core
# already builds, and the SAME query path answers it. Nothing distinguishes the
# witness, so what holds for it holds for all.
#
# No new module and no second reasoner: parrot0 has had this faculty since
# gen231, and duplicating it would have been the very thing PRINCIPLES forbids.
> if all bloops are razzies and all razzies are lazzies, are all bloops lazzies?
< Yes.

# The same helper serves the multi-sentence surface — one mechanism, two shapes.
> all blits are fumps. all fumps are gorps. are all blits gorps?
< Yes.

# ANTI-IMPOSTOR: the identical sentence shape with one link cut. A pattern-matcher
# would answer Yes; the engine actually fails to derive it.
> if all bloops are razzies and all zonks are lazzies, are all bloops lazzies?
< No.
